uson brings the story of a same-sex marriage to life in striking detail. He unearths an incredible amount of detail about the men, their sex lives, and how others responded to this information, which allows him to explore attitudes toward marriage, sex, and gender at the time. Emphasizing the instability of marriage in premodern Europe, Ferguson argues that same-sex unions should be considered part of the institution's complex and contested history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aGay menzEuropexAttitudes. 0aGay menzEuropexHistory. 0aHomophobiazEuropexHistory. 0aSame-sex marriagezEuropexHistory. 0aSame-sex marriagezRome. 0aSame-sex weddingszItalyzRomexHistoryy16th century. 4aEurope. 4aGender Studies. 4aHistory. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Italy.2bisacsh  aqueer people in renaissance Italy, Queer history of Rome, Saint John at the Latin Gate, same-sex marriage and the Catholic Church.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066749340uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150170600440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501706004423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501706004/original  a978-3-11-066749-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles